Alex Oxlade-Chamberlain's World Cup dream is on a knife-edge after his right knee buckled during England’s stormy 2-2 draw with Ecuador.

The England midfielder was substituted in the 63rd minute in a game which also saw Raheem Sterling sent off.

The Arsenal man, who was seen leaving the stadium visibly upset, crumpled in a challenge by Ecuador’s Carlos Gruezo and will undergo a scan on Thursday. Oxlade-Chamberlain’s season with his club has been disrupted by a groin injury and he had only just returned to full fitness.

